description: From Middle English umbethenken, from Old English ymbeþencan, ymbþencan (“to think about, consider, deliberate”), from ymb- (“around”) + þencan (“to think”), equivalent to um- +‎ bethink or umbe- +‎ think.

verbs.description: umbethink (third-person singular simple present umbethinks, present participle umbethinking, simple past and past participle umbethought)

entries.meaning: (dialectal, chiefly Northern England, Scotland) To recall to mind; remember; recollect.
(reflexive, dialectal, chiefly Northern England, Scotland) To consider; think about; bethink.
